			<title>Guild Wars 2 World vs World experiences</title>
			<link>http://www.graffe.com/forums/showthread.php?74048-World-vs-World-experiences&amp;goto=newpost</link>
			<pubDate>Wed, 29 Aug 2012 22:26:32 GMT</pubDate>
			<description><![CDATA[I read a lot about WvW before trying it, but was still pretty intimidating by just how much there is to it. I didn't have time to play properly yesterday so figured I would give it a shot. Ended up staying up way too late. :wtf: 
 
For starters, Shiverpeak server dominated us. I don't know if they...]]></description>
			<content:encoded><![CDATA[<div>I read a lot about WvW before trying it, but was still pretty intimidating by just how much there is to it. I didn't have time to play properly yesterday so figured I would give it a shot. Ended up staying up way too late. :wtf:<br />
<br />
For starters, Shiverpeak server dominated us. I don't know if they are a pvp server or in a different time zone, but just one of their roving bands was the same size as our entire force put together. We even had an &quot;outnumbered&quot; buff, which doesn't give you power to try and even the odds, and instead increases exp, karma, and magic find. I found a ton of green loot as a result, but it almost feels like they are encouraging you to go farm the abundance of mobs in the zones instead of put up feeble resistance. I know coordinated guilds can beat a zerg larger than themselves, but our team was anything but coordinated. Half of them didn't know to always carry supply, and the other half complained constantly about the first half.<br />
<br />
Swamp of Sorrows server seemed to sense weakness and hit whatever side Shiverpeaks was not hitting. This proved to be a poor strategy, however, as as soon as Shiverpeaks was done with us, they turned around and dominated Sorrows as well.<br />
<br />
Despite all this, the few times I was in a 1vs1 I did quite well! I sort of wish I was recording a few of those fights. Although one mesmer did gank me horribly solo, most of the times I died was because of an overabundance of bored enemies looking for something, anything, to kill would find and steamroll me in the middle of a fight. And yes, I realize WvW is not about dueling. There are objectives that don't require large forces though, and it had already become apparent to me that our forces were not capable of defending against the enemy zerg. I felt much less useful in large groups than in skirmishing. <br />
<br />
So anyway, I will now share my favorite fight of the night. It was late and I was about to go to bed, but I wanted to feel like I had done something worthwhile with my time, so went to go find one of the skillpoints on the map. In the middle of the fight, a mesmer comes along and ganks me. I still want that skill point, so I wait a few minutes but then go back, cautiously. I do not see the mesmer, but instead see an enemy guardian killing the mobs. He activates a boss and has to kite it around for a few minutes, but I opt not to gank him. I only want the skillpoint.<br />
<br />
I'm waiting up above out of his reach, and trying to stay obscured from view. His fight ends and he starts running up a nearby ramp. &quot;Don't attack me, don't attack me, don't attack me&quot; I think, not performing the opening strike, hoping he is just going somewhere else. When it finally becomes clear that he thinks I am afk or a moron or something and is about to attack me, I immediately set up the combo I described in the Combo Combat thread. I hit lightning reflexes (a ranger dodge utility) and accidentally fall off the platform we are fighting on. I'm not hurt, but have to follow suit and run all the way around the ramp to return to the fight.<br />
<br />
I call off my pet so he won't kill it, and notice I had gotten him to half life, although he is easily able to heal back before I return. Then for reasons I do not know, he decided to engage the skill point mob himself, completely ignoring the fact that I am still in the area. I decide to punish him for harassing me, and begin attacking him from behind. He turns around to engage me (he is a guardian so probably thinks he is invincible), and in the ensuing scuffle I accidentally knock him off the ledge with one of my abilities. Figuring what the heck, I then began engaging the skill point mob myself, as he had already gotten it to half life. <br />
<br />
He ends up running back to me two or three times during the fight. The first few times I intentionally knock him off the side again, forcing him to make the run once again. The final time I messed up the knockback (or he was prepared for it), but the mob knocked him off instead. :grinyes: I then finally finished it off, and left the area, not caring whether he lived or died. All I wanted was the skillpoint you jerks. The end.<br />
<br />
<a href="http://youtu.be/wLPLiV709ss?t=1m26s" target="_blank" rel="nofollow">Don't start nothing, won't be nothing! </a>:p That mesmer though, ouch. The very first person I beat was a mesmer, so it isn't the class, it was the player. <br />
<br />
I also had a fight with a ranger, that I tried to avoid (I was just scouting the area from a ledge). I just barely beat him, but still ended up dying when his friends arrived. Again, I let him have the first shot, and he did a good job keeping me at range, but I think he lost because he insisted on sticking to some mental ideal of &quot;ranger&quot;. He was using a bear pet and longbow exclusively (as far as I could tell). Bear pets no do good damage, they are only good if the enemy is stupid enough to attack it! (which actually happened to me in the beta, I was :wtf: when I realized what they were doing)<br />
<br />
Anyway I bring it up because my biggest disappointment is I was never able to knock him off a cliff. I think he must have been a huge newb or something, as he was fighting with a cliff to his back for half the fight. But because he kept snaring me, I couldn't get close enough to use my knockback at the right time, and he would (accidentally) move when I finally did. So disappointing. Would have been so epic. And with my fall damage trait I could have easily followed him down.</div>

]]></content:encoded>
