			<title>Guild Wars 2 Combat and Combos</title>
			<link>http://www.graffe.com/forums/showthread.php?74043-Combat-and-Combos&amp;goto=newpost</link>
			<pubDate>Wed, 29 Aug 2012 08:37:43 GMT</pubDate>
			<description><![CDATA[This thread is half public service announcement, half a place to put heads together about what works well together and what doesn't. Now, it's 4:30am and I should be asleep, so pardon if this isn't quite as coherent as I want it to be. 
 
*Combos* 
 
So you may have noticed that some abilities come...]]></description>
			<content:encoded><![CDATA[<div>This thread is half public service announcement, half a place to put heads together about what works well together and what doesn't. Now, it's 4:30am and I should be asleep, so pardon if this isn't quite as coherent as I want it to be.<br />
<br />
<b>Combos</b><br />
<br />
So you may have noticed that some abilities come with a descriptive line akin to &quot;Combo Field: X&quot;, where X is something like Fire, Water, Smoke, etc. etc. You may also have noticed that other abilities include the line &quot;Combo Finisher: X&quot;, where X is Projectile, or Blast, or what-have-you. If you've been wondering what these &quot;combo&quot; things are, or why little two-toned hearts pop up over peoples heads in events, this is why. Combos are one-two combinations where one spell is affected by another, gaining certain affects.<br />
<br />
For example, as an elementalist I have a staff-fire spell Lava Font, which drops down a neat little volcano o' barbecue death. However! If I stand in my own little volcano, and execute a Blast finisher, I gain a three-stack of Might. Woohoo! And since I'm in Fire attunement, I pop my Glyph heal, and have a four stack of might, and everything catches on fire. Lovely, lovely fire. For a different example, my guardian has a whirl finisher and can drop Light fields; these add a &quot;Cleansing Bolt&quot; effect to the whirl attack. Or Burning bolt, if the field is Fire. Etc. Etc.<br />
<br />
<a href="http://wiki.guildwars2.com/wiki/Combo" target="_blank" rel="nofollow">Guild Wars 2 Wiki Link</a> that should go through the various and sundry combinations of spells and abilities. I've found this is increasingly determining not only my weapons choices, but my utility skills as well; my Guardian's goto #8 skill drops a Fire field, which I can then smack with my trusty 2H hammer for Might x3, before autoattacking up to a Light field for a quick boost of Retaliation.<br />
<br />
Now, to keep this conversation ongoing; you can of course combo off of the spells that other folks drop, and I find myself trying to chain together attacks in events to set off some flashy stuff; I regularly burst water fields for a quick healing pulse for everyone, or I'll drop a Light field so all you ranged folk with projectile finishers can get some cleansing. What have you guys found that works well, both for your own benefit and for the benefit of others?</div>

]]></content:encoded>
